Keeping up with the lives, ideas, and personalities of like 300+ mutuals on twitter definitely is insanely good for your brain and expands it like London taxi drivers have their hippocampus grow. Zero irony here. It 100% makes some part of your brain literally get bigger in size.

Literally the only reason this isn't immediately obvious is because people have to pretend social media is somehow bad for you due to Soylennials whining about being addicted to it. You're literally training your memory and social faculties 24/7 365 like a top dog politician guy.

"Yeah I just have insanely detailed knowledge on 400 unique and constantly changing personalities seeing them interact w/ each other and grow year after year, this is totally not turning me into a genius 18th century type physiognomist sociologist anthropologist, it's bad for me"
